    "Let us denote withQ p (h)(t, w) = σ 2 p 2 ∂ 2 w ((1 -w 2)h(t, w)) + λ p (ω p + ε) 2 ∂ w ((w -m w (t))h(t, w)), Q ℓ (h)(t, w) = σ 2 ℓ 2 ∂ 2 w ((1 -w 2)h(t, w)) + λ ℓ (ω ℓ + ε)∂ w ((w -µ ℓ)h(t, w)),the Fokker-Planck operators appearing on the right-hand side of (44).",
